##RUNNING PROJECT

Follow these steps to set up the environment and run the AI Studio locally on your Windows machine.

### 1. Open Terminal and Navigate to the Project Folder

Open Command Prompt or PowerShell and navigate to the directory where you extracted the project:

```cmd
cd /d D:\proj

```

*(Note: If you saved the project in a different location, replace `D:\proj` with your actual folder path).*

### 2. Create a Virtual Environment

It is highly recommended to use a virtual environment to keep the project's dependencies isolated. Create a new environment specifically for Python 3.12:

```cmd
py -3.12 -m venv venv312

```

### 3. Activate the Virtual Environment

Turn on the virtual environment before installing packages or running the app:

```cmd
venv312\Scripts\activate

```

*You will know this worked when your command line prompt starts with `(venv312)`.*

### 4. Install Required Dependencies

Before running the app for the first time, you must install all the necessary AI libraries (PyTorch, Diffusers, Flask, etc.):

```cmd
pip install -r requirements.txt

```

### 5. Launch the AI Studio

Once the installation is complete, start the Flask server:

```cmd
python app6.py

```

After the engine initializes, the terminal will provide a local IP address (usually `[http://127.0.0.1:5000](http://127.0.0.1:5000)`). `Ctrl + Click` that link to open the AI Studio in your web browser!
